,0.089457,0.086744,0.072298,0.061209]},{"section":7,"text":"The gradual onset over time also points towards schizophrenia rather than something like a brief psychotic episode.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047055,0.090202,0.10338,0.10557,0.10055,0.092999,0.08922,0.084352,0.077551,0.080214,0.066642,0.062259],"unified_progress":[0.045132,0.070867,0.082516,0.093508,0.095754,0.095984,0.095995,0.095587,0.09175,0.092812,0.077749,0.062348]},{"section":8,"text":"The affect being blunt is another sign, as affective flattening is one of the negative symptoms of schizophrenia.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048212,0.088047,0.094077,0.096934,0.097221,0.095199,0.093437,0.089247,0.082266,0.080266,0.070299,0.064796],"unified_progress":[0.05045,0.072159,0.083338,0.089848,0.094609,0.098372,0.096412,0.09558,0.091128,0.087874,0.07656,0.06367]},{"section":9,"text":"The patient's age is in the 30s, which is within the typical onset range for schizophrenia.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.059215,0.091923,0.090306,0.091603,0.092932,0.096341,0.090599,0.088977,0.081939,0.08205,0.07081,0.063305],"unified_progress":[0.096335,0.09734,0.088836,0.086992,0.08665,0.088116,0.084943,0.088443,0.080384,0.077311,0.067925,0.056725]},{"section":10,"text":"The combination of positive symptoms (like thought insertion, suspiciousness) and negative symptoms (blunt affect, social withdrawal) fits.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.049092,0.089296,0.0896,0.088827,0.090382,0.092791,0.091694,0.092827,0.085364,0.083885,0.077013,0.069228],"unified_progress":[0.056744,0.082453,0.089646,0.089932,0.091812,0.096422,0.092135,0.09321,0.08782,0.084836,0.074421,0.060568]},{"section":11,"text":"Violent outbursts might be due to the patient's frustration or command hallucinations, though that's not mentioned here.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.0482